   Shouts of anger, fear, and frustration echoed throughout greater faydark.  A thick white fog swirled around a crowd of about 30 elves at canyons where the forrest meets the Butcherblock Mountains.  Many a elf was without weapons or armor and a good many more were quite armed for the coming battle.<br>    Many elves hunting in the Butcherblock Mountains had recently been driving out by a force of neutrals about 15 strong lead by an extremely powerful bard.  The bard's specialty was a tune he sang which made an elve's blood run cold with terror and flee.  As the helpless elves were fleeing the remaining force, mainly consisting of dwarves, cut them down.<br>    Having killed or driven out the majority of elves from the Butcherblock Mountains the small force was guarding the canyon letting none pass.  None from the good alliance was quite sure what would ensue.  Many thought that the neutrals would attack greater faydark, so the goods laid in wait.  Some were armed, most were not.  All were ready to fight to the death to defend their homeland.<br>    Many arguments insued on how to handle the situation and what actions to take.  Many thought we should attack now!  With 30 elves we cannot lose!  Many thought that foolishness, all who could hear the bard's sick tunes would surely fall.<br>    Several foolish dwarves, thinking to run the fleeing dwarves down, entered the greater faydark.  They were immediately slain by the force guarding the entrance.  The bard even led one of these attempts however she quickly realized the power of the party guarding the forrest and fled.  <br>   Many elves chased the dwarves and bard through the pass and were immediately slain upon entering the mountains.  This is how it stayed, a stalemate.  Neither side risking an attack for that would most likely mean defeat.<br>    Eventually a very bold elf took charge fo the force and laid out some simple plans that would hopefully ensure victory for the forces of good.  Everyone was to focus on the foul bard and root him to the ground.  When the bard fell so would the neutral army.  Several seconds later a group of 3 or 4 dwarves rushed through the pass and were slain without effort, immediately the courageous elf gave the call to attack and shouts of battle rang throughout the forrest.  Swords clashed, blood was spilled, and many a noble warrior died that day both good and neutral.  In total the bard had slain over a dozen elves before he himself was overwhelmed.  In the end fewer than 5 elves remained and every dwarf had fallen.  The battle had changed nothing, the areas around the greater faydark/butcherblock mountain pass are still being fought over and many goods and neutrals die each day defending and attacking the area.<br><br>ooc:it was a good fight, the bard was -very- cheap though everyone pretty much went LD on the good side when the bard started playing fear song but eventually we either killed em or ran em off after a few of our own deaths.  Good fight indeed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/bsullonzektavern.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=toabtn>ToabTN</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>God in Training</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/28/01 10:36:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub73.ezboard.com/fsullonzektavernfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=45.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: BBM/GFAY Fight (rp story)</span><hr size=1> Too bad you couldnt think of better word than Many to use ad nauseum. Good account though. <p><table cellSpacing="0" cellPadding="0" width="100%" border="0"><tbody><tr> <td><div align="Left"><img src="http://www.funnyhumor.btinternet.co.uk/pictures/cl015.jpg" border="0"></div></td><td><p align="center"><b>ToabTN, God i